    "When the complete trigger appears in the correct order (second example), the LLM produces the hijacked output (in green), overriding its system prompt.",
    "In contrast, an incomplete trigger (third example) or an out-of-order trigger (fourth example) fails to activate the hijack, resulting in responses that adhere to the original system prompt (in red).",
    "trigger sequence in order.",
    "Given an text prompt, T = [t 1, t 2,.",
    ", t m ], the trigger activates if and only if there exists a strictly increasing sequence of indices"
